Parallel-Simple-Dynamic 0.0.3

This module can be used for partition a big list of data into separate parts 
and processing all of them in parallel on multiple processor system.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install
	make clean

DEPENDENCIES

Class::Std;
Class::Std::Utils;
Parallel::Simple;
POSIX;

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Parallel::Simple::Dynamic

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Parallel-Simple-Dynamic

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Parallel-Simple-Dynamic

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Parallel-Simple-Dynamic

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Parallel-Simple-Dynamic/


